  "prompt": "Which keywords are associated with entry-level instructional design jobs?",
  "response": "When searching for entry-level instructional design jobs, several keywords can help you find relevant positions and tailor your resume and cover letter to match job descriptions. Here are some important keywords to consider:\n\n1. **Instructional Design**\n2. **E-Learning**\n3. **Learning and Development (L&D)**\n4. **Curriculum Development**\n5. **Educational Technology**\n6. **Learning Management System (LMS)**\n7. **Content Development**\n8. **Instructional Materials**\n9. **Course Design**\n10. **Training**\n11. **Multimedia Development**\n12. **Blended Learning**\n13. **Online Learning**\n14. **Instructional Designer I**\n15. **Junior Instructional Designer**\n16. **Entry-Level**\n17. **Instructional Technologist**\n18. **Learning Experience Designer**\n19. **Pedagogy**\n20. **ADDIE Model**\n21. **SAM Model**\n22. **Storyboarding**\n23. **Articulate Storyline**\n24. **Adobe Captivate**\n25. **Authoring Tools**\n\nUsing these keywords strategically in your job search and application materials can help you stand out as a candidate for entry-level instructional design positions.",
